ygData.messageBody:
Salutations!

Well, I hit 62 last night, or I should say early this
morning in PoJ of all places. The exp was not that
great although it did improve when we went to the
basement and it was good enough to pick up that last
9% I needed to level. Was there more to help a guildie
than anything. It was a change to be the highest in
the group, it seems like I've been the lowest for so
long. Even now most of my exp groups are mostly 63 -
65 lvl friends.

Now to try BoT. I want to get 20% in then go all AA
for a while. I hear that BoT is definatley the place
to do AA and my uber 65 Ranger hubby says we can duo
there for awesome exp. I'll see.

Also, I might be changing guilds soon. I've been in
the same guild as long as I've been playing so this
will be a change. Have not decided for 100% though. I
want to go but I want to stay.

:o)
/Hugs
Bran
